OL,3,CWoman with MS on fight for disabled
OL,4,Cpeople to have carers in hospital
OL,6,FNina, who is a wheelchair user, said:
OL,7,F"My carers are my lifeline. I have
OL,8,Fthem four times a day and they
OL,9,Fliterally do everything. They shower
OL,10,Fme in the morning, they get me out of
OL,11,Fbed, they prepare my food, they do my
OL,12,Fexercises.
OL,14,F"If I was in hospital without them it
OL,15,Fwould be horrific.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
