OL,3,CWoman with MS on fight for disabled
OL,4,Cpeople to have carers in hospital
OL,6,F"I would be anxious, depressed, I'd be
OL,7,Fstuck in a bed and I wouldn't be able
OL,8,Fto move. I would get ill, I would get
OL,9,Fa pressure sore and potentially
OL,10,Fsepsis. I would become more ill from
OL,11,Fhaving a hospital stay."
OL,13,FIn Swindon, The Great Western Hospital
OL,14,Fwelcomes carers and family members.
OL,15,FBut Nina realised not all hospitals
OL,16,Fare the same. After hearing horror
OL,17,Fstories from other disabled people,
OL,18,Fshe decided to set up an online
OL,19,Fpetition.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
